    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** leading the charge, posting a high-ceiling 74.07 score. His matchup against Warren is optimal, benefiting from a robust 14% boost due to platoon advantages and the top-of-the-order security that maximizes his counting stat potential. Close behind, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (72.39) and **Drake Baldwin** (71.83) capitalize on exploitable matchups against Quintana and Woods Richardson. **Drake Baldwin** in particular is a high-value play; while his base projection is modest, his recent form and the favorable 5.47 xERA of the opposing starter elevate his profile significantly. **Josh Lowe** rounds out our top tier with a 71.68; facing a pitcher with a disastrous 15.44 xERA, **Josh Lowe** is positioned for a breakout performance despite his lower spot in the lineup.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Jung**, who landed at 56.18. While **Josh Jung** possesses the necessary tools to outperform our utility starters, he ultimately fell short of the threshold set by **Nolan Schanuel** and **Heliot Ramos**. The optimizer leaned toward **Nolan Schanuel** due to the extreme matchup favorability against Scott, whereas **Josh Jung** faces the much tougher Flaherty. We are also monitoring **Heliot Ramos** closely; although he faces the competent McClanahan, his elite sprint speed and the base-stealing potential against a slow pitcher delivery earn him a start in our OF5 slot. \n\nRisk management remains a priority today. While our lineup avoids the most dangerous arms, we are keeping a close eye on the weather and confirmation of the lineup for **Jacob Wilson**, whose 63.93 score is predicated on his leadoff role. Should any unforeseen lineup shuffles occur, we have **Marcell Ozuna** and **Coby Mayo** ready on the bench; however, given the 5x5 Roto scarcity of stolen bases, we have prioritized players like **Jacob Wilson** and **Heliot Ramos** to ensure we maintain our competitive edge in the SB category rather than chasing raw power from **Marcell Ozuna** or **Coby Mayo**.",
